**Harold's Section:**

So a while back I looked into how make a basic frame, and if we put this code into a main method it should run a window for us.

JFrame frame = new JFrame("Testing"); //Create the frame
		//Set up the frame
		frame.setVisible(true); //Visibility
		frame.setPreferredSize(new Dimension(800,600)); //Create a dimension object to fit into the size of the window
		frame.setDefaultCloseOperation(JFrame.EXIT_ON_CLOSE); //Make it closable
		frame.pack(); //Apply size changes

		
		JLabel label = new JLabel("This is practice code without looking at outside examples.");
		label.setPreferredSize(new Dimension(200,100));
		
		frame.getContentPane().add(label,SwingConstants.CENTER);







